Kano State Executive Council has approved the constitution of a committee to draft a harmonised retirement age for teachers in the state. The Nation gathered the implementation has commenced immediately. An extension would require increase in personnel cost (salaries) and other emoluments for teachers, which the provision is not provided in the 2021 budget, so there is the need to allow the commencement of the new policy to be effective, this year, it was learnt.   Outrage over conferment of Ozo title on Igbo women     Kanu told me he didn’t issue Monday sit-at-home order…     Nigerian Army plotting execution of detained Obigbo youths,…   Read Also: Funding may delay completion of Kano-Kaduna railway project —Amaechi Commissioner for Information, Malam Muhammad, who briefed newsman on the outcome of the weekly council meeting held at the Africa House, Kano, said the committee has been mandated to constitute the necessary cause for action towards implementing “this laudable initiative” for the benefit of the education sector in the state. - Advertisement - Malam Garba pointed out that the committee will review the scheme and condition of service in the state with a view to accommodating the new retirement age of teachers from 35 years of service and 60 years of age to 40 years of service and 65 years of age, respectively.